--------------------------

"Generic Lambdas were introduced in C++14. They allow lambda parameters to be declared using `auto`, 
enabling automatic type deduction. Internally, the compiler generates a closure class with a templated `operator()`. 
They simplify generic programming and are widely used with STL algorithms."

